{{noteTA|G1=核能}}
{{他用
|subject=来源于核反應的能源（{{lang|en|nuclear power}}）
|other=使原子核结合的能量（{{lang|en|nuclear binding energy}}）
|核结合能}}
[[Image:TrigaReactorCore.jpeg|thumb]][[核反应堆|反應堆]][[TRIGA反应堆|TRIGA反应堆]]的核心近照。可以看出[[切倫科夫輻射|切倫科夫輻射]]的藍色輝光]]
[[Image:Ikata_Nuclear_Powerplant.JPG|thumb]]，有三個壓水反應堆（PWR）。冷卻是通過與海水的熱交換來實現]]
[[File:PressurizedWaterReactor.gif|400px]]運作原理]]
'''核动力'''（{{lang-en|nuclear power}}，也稱'''原子能'''或'''核能'''）是利用可控[[核反应|核反应]]来获取[[能量|能量]]<ref name="nuclearEnergy-tx">{{cite web 
 |title=Nuclear Energy 
 |work=Energy Education is an interactive curriculum supplement for secondary-school science students, funded by the U. S. Department of Energy and the Texas State Energy Conservation Office (SECO) 
 |publisher=[[U._S._Department_of_Energy|U. S. Department of Energy]] and the Texas State Energy Conservation Office (SECO) 
 |date=July 2010 
 |url=http://www.energyeducation.tx.gov/energy/section_1/topics/forms_of_energy/nuclear_energy.html 
 |accessdate=2010-07-10 
 |deadurl=yes 
 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110226114158/http://www.energyeducation.tx.gov/energy/section_1/topics/forms_of_energy/nuclear_energy.html 
 |archivedate=2011-02-26 
 }}</ref>，然后产生动力、[[热量|热量]]和[[电能|电能]]。该术语包括[[核裂变|核裂变]]，[[核衰变|核衰变]]和[[核聚变|核聚变]]。产生核电的工厂被称作[[核电站|核电站]]，将核能转化为电能的装置包括[[反应堆|反应堆]]和[[蒸汽渦輪發動機|汽轮发电机]]。核能在反应堆中被转化为[[热能|热能]]，热能将水变为[[蒸汽|蒸汽]]推动汽轮发电机组发电。

利用核反应来获取能量的原理是：当裂变材料（例如[[铀-235|铀-235]]）在受人为控制的条件下发生核裂变时，核能就会以热的形式被释放出来，这些热量会被用来驱动[[蒸汽机|蒸汽机]]。蒸汽机可以直接提供动力，也可以连接[[发电机|发电机]]来产生[[电|电]]能。世界各国军队中的某些[[潜艇|潜艇]]及[[航空母舰|航空母舰]]以核能为动力（主要是[[美國|美國]]）。

2020年全球电力有10.1%由核能发电提供<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=World Nuclear Power Reactors & Uranium Requirements|url=https://www.world-nuclear.org/information-library/facts-and-figures/world-nuclear-power-reactors-and-uranium-requireme.aspx|access-date=2021-07-27|date=2021-07|publisher=World Nuclear Association|language=en|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210727141430/https://www.world-nuclear.org/information-library/facts-and-figures/world-nuclear-power-reactors-and-uranium-requireme.aspx|archive-date=2021-07-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>。{{截至|2021|7}}，全球可运行的核电反应堆443座<ref name=":0" />，总装机容量为394.2GWe。全球在建核电反应堆54座，总装机容量为61.2GWe<ref name=":0" />。超过150艘使用[[核动力推进|核动力推进]]的舰船已被建造，由超过180个核反应堆提供动力<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.engineersgarage.com/articles/nuclear-power-plants?page=2 |title=What is Nuclear Power Plant - How Nuclear Power Plants work |3=What is Nuclear Power Reactor - Types of Nuclear Power Reactors |publisher=EngineersGarage |accessdate=2013-06-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215527/http://www.engineersgarage.com/articles/nuclear-power-plants?page=2 |archive-date=2013-10-04 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.world-nuclear.org/info/Non-Power-Nuclear-Applications/Transport/Nuclear-Powered-Ships/#.UV5yQsrpyJM |title=Nuclear-Powered Ships |3=Nuclear Submarines |publisher=World-nuclear.org |accessdate=2013-06-14 |archive-date=2013-06-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130612204746/http://www.world-nuclear.org/info/Non-Power-Nuclear-Applications/Transport/Nuclear-Powered-Ships/#.UV5yQsrpyJM |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ewp.rpi.edu/hartford/~ernesto/F2010/EP2/Materials4Students/Misiaszek/NuclearMarinePropulsion.pdf |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2015-06-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150226055625/http://www.ewp.rpi.edu/hartford/~ernesto/F2010/EP2/Materials4Students/Misiaszek/NuclearMarinePropulsion.pdf |archivedate=2015-02-26 }} Naval Nuclear Propulsion, Magdi Ragheb.
''As of 2001, about 235 naval reactors had been built''</ref>。

核动力相關的重大事故包括[[三哩岛核泄漏事故|三哩岛核泄漏事故]]（1979年）、[[切尔诺贝利核事故|切尔诺贝利核事故]]（1986年）、[[福岛第一核电站事故|福岛第一核电站事故]]（2011年）和一些核动力潜艇事故。在各種能源的事故之中，按照每个单位发电的人命损失计算，核电的安全记录優于其他几种主要的发电方式<ref name="autogenerated2007">{{cite journal|title=Electricity generation and health|pages=979–990|issn=1474-547X|journal=Lancet (London, England)|volume=370|issue=9591|date=2007-09-15|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17876910|accessdate=2019-02-13|author=Anil Markandya, Paul Wilkinson|pmid=17876910|archive-date=2020-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200425010321/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17876910|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="without the hot air">{{cite web |url= http://www.inference.phy.cam.ac.uk/withouthotair/c24/page_168.shtml |title= Dr. MacKay ''Sustainable Energy without the hot air'' |page= 168 |work= Data from studies by the Paul Scherrer Institute including non EU data |accessdate= 15 September 2012 |archive-date= 2012-09-02 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20120902001529/http://www.inference.phy.cam.ac.uk/withouthotair/c24/page_168.shtml |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>http://www.forbes.com/sites/jamesconca/2012/06/10/energys-deathprint-a-price-always-paid/ {{Wayback|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/jamesconca/2012/06/10/energys-deathprint-a-price-always-paid/ |date=20210325153905 }} with Chernobyl's total predicted linear no-threshold cancer deaths included, nuclear power is safer when compared to many alternative energy sources' immediate, death rate.</ref><ref name="theage2006">{{cite news
 |url         = http://www.theage.com.au/news/national/nuclear-power-cheaper-safer-than-coal-and-gas/2006/06/04/1149359609052.html
